6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; making
certain acts unlawful; providing penalties; providing
8 for the posting of a cash bail; authorizing courts to
dismiss criminal prosecutions under certain
9 circumstances; remanding persons to the custody of
the Department of Corrections; directing the
10 Department to notify certain federal agency to
arrange transportation; providing for codification;
11 and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 447 of Title 21, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Any person who is apprehended and arrested for violating a
19 criminal law of this state, and after determining the citizenship
20 status of the person is found to be unlawfully present in the United
21 States, shall be guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment in
22 the custody of the Department of Corrections for a term of not less
23 than five (5) years.
24
