1 B. A person arrested for a violation of this section may be
2 allowed to post a cash bond in an amount of not less than Thirty-
3 five Thousand Dollars ($35,000.00).
4 C. In lieu of the sentence of imprisonment, the court shall
5 have the authority to dismiss the criminal prosecution and issue a
6 written order discharging the person and requiring said individual
7 to return to his or her country of origin if:
8 1. The person agrees to the written order;
9 2. The person has not previously been convicted of a violent
10 crime, as provided for in Section 571 of Title 57 of the Oklahoma
11 Statutes, in this state or another state; and
12 3. The person is not charged with another felony offense.
13 Upon issuance of the written order, the court shall direct the law
14 enforcement agency having custody of the person to remand the person
15 to the custody of the Department of Corrections with instructions to
16 return the person to his or her country of origin.
17 D. Once the Department of Corrections receives custody of the
18 person, the Department of Corrections shall notify the United States
19 Customs and Border Protection of the Department of Homeland Security
20 within seven (7) days to arrange transportation for the repatriation
21 of said person back to his or her country of origin.
22 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
